I tracked down the issue up to DataSourceTransactionManagerAutoConfiguration which was creating another transaction manager as there is no bean name `transactionManager`:

```
@Bean
@ConditionalOnMissingBean(name = "transactionManager")
@ConditionalOnBean(DataSource.class)
public PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager() {
    return new DataSourceTransactionManager(this.dataSource);
}
```

I worked around this by excluding `DataSourceTransactionManagerAutoConfiguration`.
